<h2>Francis Wilfred Lawson (1842-1935)</h2>

<img src="../../../icons2/vntop.gif"/>
<p class="bc">
[<a href ="../../../index.html">Victorian Web Home</a> —> 
<a href="../../index.html">Visual Arts</a> —> 
<a href= "../index.html">Illustration</a>]</p>
</div>

<div id="main">

<p class="one">
According to Simon Houfe, Lawson, a painter and illustrator, contributed to leading periodicals, such as <span class="periodical">Belgravia</span>, <span class="periodical">The Graphic</span>, <span class="periodical">Fun</span>, and 
<span class="periodical">Punch</span>. “Reid considers his best work to be that for <span class="periodical">The Cornhill Magazine</span>” and Foze’s <span class="book">Book of Martyrs</span>” (203). —  <a href ="../../../cv/gplbio.html">George P. Landow</a>
</p>

<a href="1.html"><img src="1.jpg" height="150" border="0" class="floatright"/></a>

